		<dc:creator><![CDATA[admin]]></dc:creator>
		
		<guid isPermaLink="false">https://ea-travel.uz/blog/?post_type=blogposts&#038;p=264</guid>
				<description><![CDATA[Turkmenistan Tours is going to be the next big dream vacation for many vagabonds who have lived in isolation for so long during the past few months of the quarantine period. Luckily, the United Nations World Tourism Organisation (UNWTO) has been working behind the scenes with various countries to try and restart the global tourism industry.  <a href="https://ea-travel.uz/blog/travel-safe-secure-and-responsible-on-turkmenistan-tours-road-to-recovery-guide-by-unwto">Continue reading <span class="meta-nav">&#8594;</span></a>]]></description>
								<content:encoded><![CDATA[
<p><a href="https://ea-travel.uz/turkmenistan-tour-packages"><strong>Turkmenistan Tours</strong></a> is going to be the next big dream
vacation for many vagabonds who have lived in isolation for so long during the
past few months of the quarantine period. Luckily, the <strong>United Nations World Tourism Organisation (UNWTO)</strong> has been working
behind the scenes with various countries to try and restart the global tourism
industry. </p>



<figure class="wp-block-image"><img src="https://ea-travel.uz/blog/wp-content/uploads/2020/07/07-07-1024x616.jpg" alt="" class="wp-image-265" srcset="https://ea-travel.uz/blog/wp-content/uploads/2020/07/07-07-1024x616.jpg 1024w, https://ea-travel.uz/blog/wp-content/uploads/2020/07/07-07-300x181.jpg 300w, https://ea-travel.uz/blog/wp-content/uploads/2020/07/07-07-768x462.jpg 768w, https://ea-travel.uz/blog/wp-content/uploads/2020/07/07-07.jpg 1080w" sizes="(max-width: 1024px) 100vw, 1024px" /><figcaption> <strong>Turkmenistan Tours</strong> </figcaption></figure>



<p>The <a href="http://tourism.gov.tm/"><strong>Turkmenistan Tourism Board</strong></a> has recently attended the high-level regional meeting titled &#8220;Road to Recovery&#8221; via a video link organized by UNWTO. This high-level event was held in two-panel discussions in which the first panel discussed measures to support the travel and tourism sector and mitigate the socio-economic impact of COVID-19 while the second panel focused on best practices and effective strategies for recovery.&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; </p>



<p>According to Turkmenistan Tourism Statistics provided by <a href="https://www.unwto.org/"><strong>UNWTO</strong></a>, the decline
in international tourism for the rest of 2020 could translate to $910 billion
to $1.2 trillion in lost revenue for the industry. This is a huge setback in
the global economy and tourism industry which has faced a big blow due to the
COVID-19 crisis. People must trust the Turkmenistan Tourism&nbsp;Company which they choose to travel to the
country that provides them the complete guarantee of safety. This is where <strong>AlVoris Travels</strong> comes into action. </p>



<h4><strong>Recent Turkmenistan
Tour Updates:</strong></h4>



<ul class="wp-block-gallery columns-1 is-cropped"><li class="blocks-gallery-item"><figure><img src="https://ea-travel.uz/blog/wp-content/uploads/2020/07/077-07-1024x616.jpg" alt="" data-id="266" data-link="https://ea-travel.uz/blog/travel-safe-secure-and-responsible-on-turkmenistan-tours-road-to-recovery-guide-by-unwto/077-07" class="wp-image-266" srcset="https://ea-travel.uz/blog/wp-content/uploads/2020/07/077-07-1024x616.jpg 1024w, https://ea-travel.uz/blog/wp-content/uploads/2020/07/077-07-300x181.jpg 300w, https://ea-travel.uz/blog/wp-content/uploads/2020/07/077-07-768x462.jpg 768w, https://ea-travel.uz/blog/wp-content/uploads/2020/07/077-07.jpg 1080w" sizes="(max-width: 1024px) 100vw, 1024px" /></figure></li></ul>



<ul><li>All
international flights for <a href="https://ea-travel.uz/turkmenistan-destinations"><strong>Turkmenistan Tours</strong></a> have
been suspended until 20 July. Also, nationals and residents arriving from
overseas are required to stay in a quarantine period for 14 days after landing
from Turkmenistan Flights.</li><li>The
Turkmenistan Tourism&nbsp;Arrivals,
for the time being, have been suspended.
It is likely to resume in July. </li><li>For
your absolute Turkmenistan
Tourism&nbsp; Safety, police
checkpoints have been established around the country, and drivers may be
stopped for a temperature check.</li><li>Apart
from this, passengers arriving in Turkmenistan:<ul><li>must have a medical
certificate stating a negative Coronavirus (COVID-19) test result issued at
most 72 hours before departure by the competent authority of the county of
residency; and<br>
– are subject to be tested for COVID-19 on arrival and to self-isolation for 14
days.</li></ul></li></ul>



<h4><strong>Things To Know Before Starting Your Turkmenistan Tours</strong></h4>



<figure class="wp-block-image"><img src="https://ea-travel.uz/blog/wp-content/uploads/2020/07/0777-07-1-1024x616.jpg" alt="" class="wp-image-275" srcset="https://ea-travel.uz/blog/wp-content/uploads/2020/07/0777-07-1-1024x616.jpg 1024w, https://ea-travel.uz/blog/wp-content/uploads/2020/07/0777-07-1-300x181.jpg 300w, https://ea-travel.uz/blog/wp-content/uploads/2020/07/0777-07-1-768x462.jpg 768w, https://ea-travel.uz/blog/wp-content/uploads/2020/07/0777-07-1.jpg 1080w" sizes="(max-width: 1024px) 100vw, 1024px" /><figcaption> <strong>Turkmenistan Tours</strong> </figcaption></figure>



<p>Before starting your Turkmenistan Tours here are few things you should
know related to Turkmenistan Tourism&nbsp; Facts and safety to travel securely
with AlVoris Travels:<strong></strong></p>



<ul><li><strong>Consider Your Risk Factors</strong></li></ul>



<p>Consider the risk
factors for yourself and those traveling with you, before planning a trip. Solo
tours and private tours are highly recommended instead of traveling with family
or groups during the pandemic.</p>



<ul><li><strong>Travel rules and regulations</strong></li></ul>



<p>It’s essential to
abide by regulations and rules prescribed by the country. You can speak to our
travel experts to learn in detail about the travel restrictions and regulations
being followed by Turkmenistan. </p>



<ul><li><strong>Transportation Safety</strong></li></ul>



<p>Safety in traveling
is essential. You must follow the social distancing measures while taking your
seats on a bus or booking your flight tickets. Maintain 6 feet distance from
other travelers and consider waiting in long lines for several hours for the check
at the airport for your safety. </p>



<ul><li><strong>Health And Safety</strong></li></ul>



<p>Pack enough personal
protection equipment including face masks, gloves, and hand sanitizer. Apart
from this, you must make sure to wash your hands regularly or sanitize it in
case soap and water aren’t available. Consult a medical professional
immediately in case you have signs or symptoms of the virus. </p>



